Extract Mode for a Marketing Cloud Engagement Data Extension in Data Cloud

Marketing Cloud Engagement Connector Extract mode dictates how Data Cloud exports and imports data from Marketing Cloud Engagement.

Data Cloud Engagement connector communicates with the source system on your behalf, but sometimes needs your help on source-specific concepts like extract settings. Engagement generates datasets based on the extract setting that you choose. If you choose data that reflects only new or updated records, there’s increased efficiency because there are fewer extracted records for the run.

Refresh Mode in Data Cloud dictates how incoming data interacts with the data lake object (DLO). Use Refresh Mode to indicate if incoming data adds or updates previously sent data or replaces it with a new snapshot.

Extract settings correspond to how Engagement exports data. Refresh settings represent how that data is imported. If the Full Refresh extract is configured for Engagement, choose a Full Refresh import in Data Cloud. And a delta extract, reflecting new or updated records, is associated with an Upsert import in Data Cloud.

NOTE If you can’t use Upsert, you can’t change the Refresh settings. When the data stream was provisioned, the Refresh mode was set. Even deleting the data stream and recreating it, still uses that Refresh mode.

To extract data from Engagement, use a Full Refresh for all data to be available all the time. To extract data incrementally, use Numeric CDC or Date Time CDC. You can anchor each extract to the high-water mark for a column in the raw data.

Full Refresh
Learn more about the Full Refresh extract method in Data Cloud and when to use it.
Delta Extract
Marketing Cloud Engagement supports two types of incremental extracts: delta extract by date and by number.
